===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|welth||happiness, prosperity|lang=enm}}, alteration (due to similar words in {{term|-th|lang=enm}}: compare {{term|helth||health|lang=enm}}) of {{term|wele||wealth, well-being, weal|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|wela||wealth, prosperity|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|wilēn||wala-||wula-|well-being, prosperity|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|wel-|good, best|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{osx}} {{term|welo||weal|lang=osx}}, {{goh}} {{term|wela|lang=goh}}, {{term|wola||weal, well-being|tr={{de}} {{term|Wohl|lang=de}}|lang=goh}}, {{da}} {{term|vel||weal, welfare|lang=da}}. More at {{l|en|weal}}, {{l|en|well}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{obsolete}} Weal; welfare; prosperity; good; well-being; happiness; joy.
# Riches; valuable material possessions.
# A [[great]] [[amount]]; an [[abundance]] or [[plenty]].
#: ''She brings a '''wealth''' of knowledge to the project.''
# [[power|Power]], of the kind associated with a great deal of money.

